001package reciprocal.number.complex;
002
003import static java.util.Objects.hash;
004import static java.util.Objects.requireNonNull;
005
006import java.io.Serial;
007import java.math.BigDecimal;
008import java.math.BigInteger;
009import org.jetbrains.annotations.NotNull;
010import org.jetbrains.annotations.Nullable;
011
012/**
013 * Base class for complex numbers
014 *
015 * @param <N> {@link Number}
016 * @param <T> {@link AbstractComplex}
017 * @param <Q> quotient
018 * @param <A> absolute value
019 * @param <P> {@link AbstractPolarForm}
020 * @since 0.0.1
021 */
022public abstract class AbstractComplex<N extends Number, T extends AbstractComplex<N, T, Q, A, P>, Q, A, P>
023    extends Number {
024    @Serial
025    private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;
026
027    private final @NotNull N real;
028    private final @NotNull N imaginary;
029
030    /**
031     * Constructor
032     *
033     * @param real real part
034     * @param imaginary imaginary part
035     * @throws NullPointerException when {@code real == null}
036     * @throws NullPointerException when {@code imaginary == null}
037     * @since 0.0.1
038     */
039    protected AbstractComplex(final @NotNull N real, final @NotNull N imaginary) {
040        this.real = requireNonNull(real, "real");
041        this.imaginary = requireNonNull(imaginary, "imaginary");
042    }
043
044    /**
045     * Indicates if this is invertible
046     *
047     * @return {@link Boolean}
048     * @since 0.0.1
049     */
050    public abstract boolean isInvertible();
051
052    /**
053     * Indicates if this is not invertible
054     *
055     * @return {@link Boolean}
056     * @since 0.0.1
057     */
058    public final boolean isNotInvertible() {
059        return !isInvertible();
060    }
061
062    /**
063     * Calculates the sum
064     *
065     * @param summand summand
066     * @return sum
067     * @throws NullPointerException when {@code summand == null}
068     * @since 0.0.1
069     */
070    public abstract @NotNull T add(@NotNull T summand);
071
072    /**
073     * Calculates the difference
074     *
075     * @param subtrahend subtrahend
076     * @return difference
077     * @throws NullPointerException when {@code subtrahend == null}
078     * @since 0.0.1
079     */
080    public abstract @NotNull T subtract(@NotNull T subtrahend);
081
082    /**
083     * Calculates the product
084     *
085     * @param factor factor
086     * @return product
087     * @throws NullPointerException when {@code factor == null}
088     * @since 0.0.1
089     */
090    public abstract @NotNull T multiply(@NotNull T factor);
091
092    /**
093     * Calculates the quotient
094     *
095     * @param divisor divisor
096     * @return quotient
097     * @throws NullPointerException when {@code divisor == null}
098     * @throws NullPointerException when divisor is not invertible
099     * @since 0.0.1
100     */
101    public abstract @NotNull Q divide(@NotNull T divisor);
102
103    /**
104     * Calculates the power
105     *
106     * @param exponent exponent
107     * @return power
108     * @since 0.0.1
109     */
110    public abstract @NotNull Q pow(int exponent);
111
112    /**
113     * Calculates the negated
114     *
115     * @return negated
116     * @since 0.0.1
117     */
118    public abstract @NotNull T negate();
119
120    /**
121     * Calculates the inverted
122     *
123     * @return inverted
124     * @since 0.0.1
125     */
126    public abstract @NotNull Q invert();
127
128    /**
129     * Calculates the absolute value
130     *
131     * @return absolute value
132     * @since 0.0.1
133     */
134    public abstract @NotNull A abs();
135
136    /**
137     * Calculates the conjugate
138     *
139     * @return conjugate
140     * @since 0.0.1
141     */
142    public abstract @NotNull T conjugate();
143
144    /**
145     * Calculates the argument
146     *
147     * @return argument
148     * @throws IllegalStateException when this is not invertible
149     * @since 0.0.1
150     */
151    public abstract @NotNull A argument();
152
153    @Override
154    public final int intValue() {
155        return real.intValue();
156    }
157
158    @Override
159    public final long longValue() {
160        return real.longValue();
161    }
162
163    @Override
164    public final float floatValue() {
165        return real.floatValue();
166    }
167
168    @Override
169    public final double doubleValue() {
170        return real.doubleValue();
171    }
172
173    /**
174     * Returns this as {@link BigInteger}
175     *
176     * @return {@link BigInteger}
177     * @since 0.0.1
178     */
179    public abstract @NotNull BigInteger toBigInteger();
180
181    /**
182     * Returns this as {@link BigDecimal}
183     *
184     * @return {@link BigDecimal}
185     * @since 0.0.1
186     */
187    public abstract @NotNull BigDecimal toBigDecimal();
188
189    /**
190     * Returns this as polar form
191     *
192     * @return polar form
193     * @throws IllegalStateException when this is not invertible
194     * @since 0.0.1
195     */
196    public abstract @NotNull P toPolarForm();
197
198    /**
199     * Returns if this is equal by comparing to other
200     *
201     * @param other other
202     * @return {@link Boolean}
203     * @throws NullPointerException when {@code other == null}
204     * @since 0.0.1
205     */
206    public abstract boolean equalsByComparing(@NotNull T other);
207
208    /**
209     * Returns if this is not equal by comparing to other
210     *
211     * @param other other
212     * @return {@link Boolean}
213     * @throws NullPointerException when {@code other == null}
214     * @since 0.0.1
215     */
216    public final boolean doesNotEqualByComparing(final @NotNull T other) {
217        return !equalsByComparing(other);
218    }
219
220    /**
221     * Binary + operator for Groovy and Kotlin
222     *
223     * @param summand summand
224     * @return sum
225     * @throws NullPointerException when {@code summand == null}
226     * @since 0.0.1
227     */
228    public final @NotNull T plus(final @NotNull T summand) {
229        return add(summand);
230    }
231
232    /**
233     * Binary - operator for Groovy and Kotlin
234     *
235     * @param subtrahend subtrahend
236     * @return difference
237     * @throws NullPointerException when {@code subtrahend == null}
238     * @since 0.0.1
239     */
240    public final @NotNull T minus(final @NotNull T subtrahend) {
241        return subtract(subtrahend);
242    }
243
244    /**
245     * Binary / operator for Groovy and Kotlin
246     *
247     * @param divisor divisor
248     * @return quotient
249     * @throws NullPointerException when {@code divisor == null}
250     * @throws IllegalArgumentException when divisor is not invertible
251     * @since 0.0.1
252     */
253    public final @NotNull Q div(final @NotNull T divisor) {
254        return divide(divisor);
255    }
256
257    /**
258     * Binary ** operator for Groovy
259     *
260     * @param exponent exponent
261     * @return power
262     * @since 0.0.1
263     */
264    public final @NotNull Q power(final int exponent) {
265        return pow(exponent);
266    }
267
268    /**
269     * Calculates the square of the absolute value
270     *
271     * @return square of the absolute value
272     * @since 0.0.1
273     */
274    protected abstract @NotNull N absPow2();
275
276    /**
277     * Real
278     *
279     * @return real
280     * @since 0.0.1
281     */
282    public final @NotNull N getReal() {
283        return real;
284    }
285
286    /**
287     * Imaginary
288     *
289     * @return imaginary
290     * @since 0.0.1
291     */
292    public final @NotNull N getImaginary() {
293        return imaginary;
294    }
295
296    @Override
297    public final int hashCode() {
298        return hash(real, imaginary);
299    }
300
301    @Override
302    public final boolean equals(final @Nullable Object obj) {
303        if (this == obj) {
304            return true;
305        }
306        if (obj == null || getClass() != obj.getClass()) {
307            return false;
308        }
309        final AbstractComplex<?, ?, ?, ?, ?> other = (AbstractComplex<?, ?, ?, ?, ?>) obj;
310        return real.equals(other.getReal()) && imaginary.equals(other.getImaginary());
311    }
312
313    @Override
314    public final @NotNull String toString() {
315        return getClass().getSimpleName() + "{real=" + real + ", imaginary=" + imaginary + "}";
316    }
317}
